item.title: The Onion Movie Trailer: Finally, a Kentucky Fried Movie for Our Generation
item.description: Tagline: “Only one news organization has the guts to tell it like it is…” Translation: …or at least compile some semi-hilarious crap into a 90-minute DVD collection of comedy skits, one of which stars Steven Seagal! The Verdict: The consistently funny Onion News Network has finally made completed its *long overdue* feature-length movie, and it’s headed straight to DVD, presumably because bongs aren’t allowed in movie theaters. From this trailer (which has apparently been around for a little while), it’s still unclear whether it’ll be a collection of short, funny clips sustained by a barely-there plot (like “Weird Al“‘s 1989 classic UHF), or a collection of short, funny clips without any plot whatsoever (like The Kentucky Fried Movie or Robert Altman’s Short Cuts).

item.title: Cleveland Kidnapper Ariel Castro Found Dead In Prison Cell
item.description: Convicted rapist and kidnapper Ariel Castro was found hanging in his jail cell on Tuesday evening (Sept. 3), according to the Associate Press. Prison officials at Correctional Reception Center in Orient found him in his cell and medical staff tried to administer CPR. He was then immediately transferred to a hospital where he was pronounced dead. Officials are calling this a suicide. Spokeswoman JoEllen Smith of the Ohio Department of Corrections released a statement via Cleveland’s 19 Action News: Inmate Ariel Castro was found hanging in his cell this evening at 9:20 pm at the Correctional Reception Center in Orient.

item.title: Wolfgang Schuble Obituary
item.description: Wolfgang Schäuble, a stalwart German politician, minister, and statesman, whose remarkable political journey spanned over five decades, bid farewell on December 26, 2023, succumbing to cancer at the age of 81, surrounded by his family. Born in Freiburg in 1942, Schäuble emerged as a leading figure within the conservative Christian Democrats (CDU). His political odyssey began in 1972 when he entered parliament, and he went on to secure victory in his Offenburg constituency in every subsequent election, earning the distinction of being Germany’s longest-serving postwar parliamentarian.
